answer.p:
Occasionally, the regular expression must be dynamically generated
      by a worker thread, so this technique doesn't work. In this case, you can
      import re in every worker thread:

answer.source:
class TestRunner:
  def __init__(self):
    import re

  def __call__(self):
    # __call__ is executed by worker threads
    p = re.compile('a.b', re.IGNORECASE)
    # use p

